Calculation of estimates of construction sites in the Russian Federation will occur in a new way
Issues of pricing, regulation of the construction industry, as well as problems of connection to networks, the Federal Antimonopoly Service takes special control.
The FAS has created an expert council for the development of competition in the construction sector.
At its meeting, the head of the Department of control of housing and communal services, construction and natural resources of the FAS Vadim Solovyov said that "today's calculation of the estimate of construction sites is absolutely incomprehensible."
The regulatory framework makes pricing opaque and can lead to an unreasonable construction price, the FAS said.
And they propose to determine the cost of construction of state-owned facilities at the design stage on the basis of market prices of constructive solutions instead of the estimated norms and unit prices for technological operations applied today.
These proposals are included in the road map and are currently under consideration in the Ministry of Construction.
“The replacement of traditional estimated documentation in construction with calculations of structural elements should lead to less corruption in the industry,” Vadim Solovyov explained to RGB.
After all, now every bolt and nut is calculated in the estimate, and it is not always possible to check everything, so sometimes unscrupulous construction companies can bury "whole tractors" in the documentation.
In Minnesota, I agree.
"The first developments on the transition to the calculation of the cost of structural elements already exist: methods have been developed for calculating the prices for constructive solutions, compiling estimates for these indicators," Elena Zhukova, head of the department of urban planning and architecture of the Ministry of Construction, told RGB.
The field of road construction was chosen as a pilot.
However, experts believe that the problem is much more serious.
As the head of the construction company "Profi-invest" Anatoly Demyanko told "RGB", the estimated standards are outdated, but another mechanism has not yet been offered to the business.
“As for the proposed calculations on structural elements, in practice it is difficult to implement, since the construction of buildings often use completely different technologies,” he said.
It is no secret that the Styrofoam market is developing largely due to government orders.
According to Ekaterina Lezina, the Chairman of the Board of the Expert Community of State Order Professionals, today the state is the most solvent customer.
Vladimir Malakhov, deputy director for engineering of the industrial capital construction center of Rosatom, drew attention to the fact that today the market is conditionally divided into companies that have access to a portfolio of contracts and companies that have monopolistic competencies and do not allow competitors in this field.
He believes that the creation of a transparent market is possible only if access to contracts is protected as much as possible from someone’s managerial influence.
At the expert council, it was proposed to form a state order system in such a way that the same performer is not entitled to receive more than one contract worth more than 1 billion rubles or several contracts worth more than 1 billion rubles.
The Ministry believes that this approach should be evaluated in terms of the impact on business, as well as the effectiveness of construction management.
As explained by Elena Zhukova, in this case, it will be necessary to give the customer the functions of a general contractor, which will lead to an increase in the staffing of the customer and budget costs for its maintenance.
At the same time, the customer's specialists will have to have the knowledge to assess the quality of the work performed by the contracting organizations, as well as their safety.
Often, with such a breakdown, it will be necessary to determine who will be responsible for the safety of the facility as a whole.
In addition, this approach may lead to the outflow of highly qualified participants in public procurement due to disinterest in receiving a state order for incomplete work and a small contract amount.
