Will Kiev “Rosneft” compensate $140 million in losses?
The head of Rosneft Igor Sechin said that the company estimates the damage from the shelling of the Lisichansk refinery in Ukraine at $140 million.
He said this in an interview with Spiegel.
“We estimate the damage at $140 million and will negotiate with the Ukrainian government to pay compensation,” Sechin said.
According to him, the commissioning of the Lisichansk Refinery, which was modernized by the company, was planned in 2014.
However, part of the plant was destroyed by Ukrainian artillery.
“There were no fighting, there were no ‘grounded rebels’, but Ukrainian artillery destroyed part of the industrial facility.
In addition, the technological oil pumped into the pipes is missing,” he said.
Recall that on July 18, in connection with the shelling of the Lisichansk refinery, an oil storage tank burned down and the buildings of two warehouses were destroyed.
Lisichansk Refinery is the main oil refinery in Ukraine, the first stage of the enterprise was put into operation in October 1976.
The total capacity of the Lisichansk refinery is about 7 million tons of oil raw materials per year.
The plant is able to produce fuel of the Euro-4 standard, as well as diesel fuel of the Euro-5 standard.
In March 2012, oil supplies to the Lisichansk refinery were suspended due to its unprofitability.
The company decided to start repairs.
A year later, Rosneft received the Lisichansk refinery together with other Ukrainian assets of TNK-BP.
