Twitter has tried to become more interesting for new users
Twitter’s microblogging service has changed the registration process for users in order to engage new members more quickly in active interaction with the platform.
This measure should reduce the number of people who have abandoned their microblogs.
Now, new Twitter users will be browsing a large number of accounts recommended by the service during registration in order to immediately compile their reading circle.
Recommendations are drawn up on the basis of the interests indicated in the registration.
At the same time, Twitter automatically sets a subscription checkbox for all automatically selected accounts.
Because of this, the user will have to manually remove ticks, so as not to read those who are not interested in him.
If previously users of the microblogging service saw only avatars of recommended users, now Twitter displays a sample of one of the blogger’s popular tweets to help make an impression about a person.
This is the biggest change to Twitter’s registration page in three years.
Recently, Twitter is actively working to modernize the service.
Such activity is associated, first of all, with the ongoing attempts of the service to achieve breakeven.
In 2014, the microblogging service faced a slowdown in the growth of the user base and a drop in reader activity.
At the moment, the company desperately needs more loyal consumers, who, once in a while, would stay for a long time.
This is the only way to ensure a stable flow of advertising funds.
