The massive hacking of star accounts may have been due to a vulnerability in the Find My Phone app.
A potential scenario of events described resource The Next Web.
On the resource Github was published a script in the language Python, which allowed you to select passwords for the Find My Phone service of Apple.
This service allows you to track the location of the iPhone.
It uses the same Apple ID username and password as the Apple iCloud cloud from which photos of celebrities were stolen.
The script allowed the search method to recognize the password from Find My Phone.
In this method, all kinds of character combinations are entered sequentially, starting with the most commonly used passwords.
The author of the script claimed that in the Find My Phone service the number of entered password options is unlimited.
If the security system is properly organized after several failed attempts to enter the wrong password, the account should be blocked and inform the user of the hacking attempt.
Because of the vulnerability, users did not receive any messages about trying to find a password for their account.
The hackers learned the password from Apple ID and used it to access iCloud.
